Interface RangeQuery<O>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - Object type
    All Superinterfaces:
    DatabaseQuery
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDistanceRangeQuery, AbstractRefiningIndex.AbstractRangeQuery, CoverTree.CoverTreeRangeQuery, EuclideanRStarTreeRangeQuery, InMemoryIDistanceIndex.IDistanceRangeQuery, InMemoryInvertedIndex.ArcCosineRangeQuery, InMemoryInvertedIndex.CosineRangeQuery, InMemoryLSHIndex.Instance.LSHRangeQuery, LinearScanDistanceRangeQuery, LinearScanEuclideanDistanceRangeQuery, LinearScanPrimitiveDistanceRangeQuery, MetricalIndexRangeQuery, MinimalisticMemoryKDTree.KDTreeRangeQuery, PartialVAFile.PartialVAFileRangeQuery, ProjectedIndex.ProjectedRangeQuery, RStarTreeRangeQuery, SimplifiedCoverTree.CoverTreeRangeQuery, SmallMemoryKDTree.KDTreeRangeQuery, VAFile.VAFileRangeQuery

    public interface RangeQuery<O>
extends DatabaseQuery
    The interface for range queries, that can return all objects within the specified radius. Do not confuse this with rectangular window queries, which are also commonly called "range queries".
    Author:
    Erich Schubert
